---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Azure Data Project Platform"
  description="Azure-hosted technical data project platform for SQL, Python, R, pipelines, dashboards, and analytics engineering demos."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Azure-hosted technical project platform</p>
      <h1>Cloud data demos built around safe, synthetic project workflows.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        A public site for deployed technical data projects covering SQL, Python/R, Azure, data
        pipelines, dashboards, data quality, analytics engineering, and reproducible methods.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href="/projects/">View projects</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/azure-architecture/">Architecture plan</a>
      </div>
      <div class="chip-row" aria-label="Focus areas">
        <span class="chip">SQL</span>
        <span class="chip">Python/R</span>
        <span class="chip">Azure</span>
        <span class="chip">ETL pipelines</span>
        <span class="chip">Dashboards</span>
        <span class="chip">Data quality</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="system-panel" aria-label="Planned platform flow">
      <header><span></span><span></span><span></span></header>
      <pre><code>Azure Static Web Apps
  -> project pages
  -> Blob Storage sample files
  -> Python ETL in Azure Functions
  -> Azure SQL curated tables
  -> dashboard/report outputs</code></pre>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="band-inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Platform intent</p>
          <h2>Technical work first.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          This site is intentionally not a resume page. It is a public technical workspace for
          showing cloud data architecture, transformation logic, validation design, and visual
          outputs without exposing private operational information.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Safe data boundary</h3>
          <p>All demo datasets, screenshots, schemas, and metrics are synthetic or public-safe.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Azure deployment path</h3>
          <p>Static site front end with low-cost serverless ETL and storage components behind it.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Method documentation</h3>
          <p>Each project will document objective, pipeline, transformations, checks, outputs, and code.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
